tafsir[4]{c,v,t}:
  21,73,"21:72"
  21,75,"21:74"
  21,77,"21:76"
  21,78,"Commentaryنَفَشَتْ فِيهِ غَنَمُ الْقَوْمِ the goats of the people wandered therein grazing - 21:78). In Arabic language the word نَفَشَ (translated above as 'wandering and grazing' ) means an animal getting into a field at night and damaging it."